modules.description: Provides functions to read from and write to the console, handle input events, and configure console output settings. Works with byte sequences, event records, and configuration parameters specific to Solo5 environments. Used to implement interactive command-line interfaces and logging mechanisms in unikernel applications.

Provides asynchronous read and write operations for network flows, including handling of buffer sequences and error states. Works with Cstruct.t buffers, custom error types, and a flow handle type. Used to manage console communication, ensuring reliable data transmission and proper connection termination.
